    <table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%">
    <tr>
        <td id="descriptionArea">
            <p><b>Issue Description:</b> The use of sysdate in SQL statements lacks fractional seconds, causing Oracle to randomly select between transactions with identical timestamps, resulting in incorrect guarantee calculations.</p>

<p><b>Technical Solution:</b> The fix involves replacing sysdate with <b>local timestamp</b> in all relevant XML files and updating existing data to include fractional seconds, using calculation order as the fractional component.</p>

<p><b>Testing Requirements:</b> Swapnil from the QA automation team suggested for validation, and client services to perform front-end calculator checks</p>

<p><b>Mitigation Process:</b> Ganesh created a spreadsheet calculator which has been provide to client service for manual validation, allowing CSR to check calculations until the fix is deployed. Ganesh can assist with checks if needed.</p>
            <br/>
        </td>
    </tr>
    </table>

